DISCLAIMERS Since some of the listed capacity is for formatting and not available for data storage, the actual available memory capacity may be less than the total listed storage capacity. Factory default setting is 1GB=1,000,000,000 Bytes Displayed in PC as 1,000,000,000 Bytes/1024/1024/1024=0.93GB Example-256GB SSD: Factory capacity: 256x1000x1000x1000=256,000,000,000B=256GB Actual capacity: 256,000,000,000B/1024/1024/1024=256GB x 0.93=238GB Transmission speed will vary according to different hardware/software conditions, therefore the data can only use for basic reference.Newly purchased SSD is blank, so you will need to format them in Disk Management before you can use them. Initial formatting involves locating the volume and creating partitions in Disk Management. After performing the formatting process, our computer will be able to recognize and use it. lt is recommended to format in the windows operating system and use NTFS format.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I made a scathing review of this because my laptop would not recognize the device. I dove a little deeper and found out I had to go into disk management and format the device. It's simple but not intuitive. I had to do a youtube tutorial to get the proper steps. The end result is that this device works and it pretty fast...if I have any problems, I'll edit it.Please note that you only get 465 usable GB, not the 500 that they advertise but I believe this is a pretty standard practice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars New life for old laptop.
reviews.reviewText: My old HP ProBook has been gathering dust. Old, slow, 500GB hard drive... Took forever to boot up. It even has DDR3 memory!I decided to try making it useful on the cheap, so I bought this 1TB drive. The results are more than worth it.CrystalDiskMark has it as 10 times as fast as my old hard drive.The difference is amazing.It went from "Hit power button, go make cup of coffee, come back and log in" to "Hit power button, *blip* Log in".Every program loads faster, as well.So now it's been dusted and cleaned up and sits on my desk again, ready for daily use. I'm going to add more RAM, and will probably buy a larger FikWot drive for it, maybe a 2TB this time.Also, the SATA connector is pretty solid and doesn't flex like that expensive Crucial SSD did before it broke.Don't know how long it will last, but it's already lasted longer than that Crucial did.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great if you need one of this type for an upgrade
reviews.reviewText: When looking to upgrade an old Lenovo Ideapad with a built-in 32GB storage it required an older technology M.2. The M/.2 would not accept the current NVME so I chose this and the 1TB NAND / NGFF fir perfectly and allowed me to replace the onboard storage with this as the primary device. I was unable to add this as a logical extension to the existing HDD, but that's a lenovo fault for soldering memory to the board instead of making it modular.With this unit installed, we are now able to boot from a 1 TB drive and able to install Windows updates that were required simply to operate the machine. by using this NAND M.2, it is breathing new life into a machine that had become unusable and out of the most basic storage capabilities.BOTTOM LINE: If you need an older NGFF to upgrade an older laptop - this has proven to be a great solution.Reviewed:Fikwot FN203 1TB M.2 SATA SSD - SLC Cache 3D NAND TLC SATA III 6Gb/s M.2 2280 NGFF Internal Solid State Drive, Up to 550MB/s, Compatible with Ultrabooks, Tablet Computers and Mini PCs

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Only worked for 5 months
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this drive to put into a pc that I was giving to my son's friend. After 5 months I received a call from him stating that he can no longer play his games because his pc can no longer find his driver. I have tried it in my on pc and it doesn't even appear as a driver at all. I have sent a message to Fikwot.com to see what can be done to correct this issue. I understand that these things do happen I just hope that the Fikwot.com will stand behind their product and make it right. I would understand if it has been more then a year, but for it to only work for 5 months.
I tested three major brands for damaged sectors. The only one that tested clean was Fikwot. Both 128 and 256 gb.
